@NODE GLOB "Global Conventions"

Clear - 
    All "CLEAR" requestors require you to double click so you don't 
    accidentily clear important fields or kill important information.

NPC - 
    Non-Player Characters.  In other words, characters or monsters in the 
    game.
        
PC - 
    Player Characters.  The characters controlled by the user.
        
Hit Point(s) - 
    This basically is how much damage a character can take before he/she 
    dies.
            
@ENDNODE

@NODE "EDITG" "Edit Game"

    This will allow you to load up a module and edit it.  If the module
    requires a @{"password" link "Password"} you will be prompted and will need to enter the
    correct password.  At this point you will go to the game creation
    menu.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Game Target"

    Once a game target is picked up (object) or killed (creature) the
    @{"winning picture file" link WGAME} is shown and the @{"winning sound file"link SWGAM} is played 
    and the game is reset.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Wishlist"

1) Allow one to make a 3D dungeon.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "PGAME" "Play Game"

    This option brings up a requestor that asks which module to play.  Just
    use the requestor to pick the file name of the module you wish to play
    and start adventuring!
    
@ENDNODE


@NODE "SGAME" "Save Game"

    This button allows you to save a game that you have made.  Before you
    save a game, you must enter a @{"password" link password}.  Then just click on the big save
    game button.  ADS will check for any errors for you and print them in 
    the message window.  If the errors scroll off of the screen you can use
    the Up/Down buttons on the upper left hand corner of the screen to go 
    back to check what they were.  If there are any errors, the game will 
    not save and you will have to go back and fix them before you can save 
    your game.
    
@ENDNODE

@NODE "QUIT" "Quit ADS"

    This quits ADS, DUH!!
    
@ENDNODE

